=== Groovy Task ===

==== Functionality ====
{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.task.GroovyTask
| type = 'DESCRIPTION'
}}

The groovy script requires the method: '''go()'''

==== Configuration Settings ====

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.task.GroovyTask
| type = CONFIGURATION
}}

==== Quick guide ====

Save this code example as groovy file(e.g. example.groovy) in the scripts folder.

<source>
public void go() throws Exception{
	throw new Exception("Example");
}
</source>

Note: The Groovy script needs into the folder: "scripts"
* Go to [[Admin:Tasks|Recurring Tasks]]
* Click '''Add Task'''
# Choose in '''Task''': GroovyTask
# Enter in '''Identifer''' a name(e.g. exampleTask)
# Enter in '''Scheduler''' the time in minutes(e.g. 60)
# Enter/Choose in '''Script''' the script relative to the scripts folder (e.g. Example.groovy)
# Click '''Submit'''
<img src="../images/help/TaskScheduler/AddGroovyTask.png" alt="IMAGE:Add Groovy Task" style="border:1px solid black;"/>

Note: It is possible to create the go() method with arguments:
<source>
public void go(String s) throws Exception{
	throw new Exception(s);
}
</source>